tool.summary: Create a concentric circle from a center with two rings depicting a minimum range and a maximum range from a table.
tool.usage:
• One Input Center Feature must be used at a minimum.

  • The Input Table must include:

    • A name field (string) that uniquely identifies each range type.

    • A minimum range field (number) for the nearest distance.

    • A maximum range field (number) for the farthest distance.

  • The minimum and maximum range values must be positive numbers.

  • The World Azimuthal Equidistant (WKID 54032) projected coordinate system is the default if no Spatial Reference is selected.
